    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Matar Paneer is a popular North Indian curry dish made with green peas (matar) and cottage cheese (paneer) cooked in a spiced tomato-onion gravy. It's usually served with roti or rice.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>‚è±Ô∏è <strong>30 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>200g paneer (cubed)</li>
        <li>1 cup green peas</li>
        <li>2 onions (chopped)</li>
        <li>2 tomatoes (pureed)</li>
        <li>1 tsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp red chili powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp garam masala</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp cumin seeds</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>2 tbsp oil</li>
        <li>Fresh coriander for garnish</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Heat oil in a pan, add cumin seeds and let them splutter.</li>
        <li>Add onions and saut√© until golden brown.</li>
        <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and cook until raw smell disappears.</li>
        <li>Add tomato puree, turmeric, red chili powder, salt, and cook till oil separates.</li>
        <li>Add green peas and cook for 5-7 minutes. Add some water if needed.</li>
        <li>Add paneer cubes and simmer for 5 more minutes.</li>
        <li>Sprinkle garam masala and mix gently.</li>
        <li>Garnish with fresh coriander and serve hot with roti, naan, or rice.</li>
    </ol>
